# Django Conventions

## Project Structure

```
project_root/
├── manage.py
├── project/             # Django project config
│   ├── settings.py
│   ├── urls.py
│   └── wsgi.py
├── app/                 # Main application
│   ├── models.py
│   ├── views.py
│   ├── urls.py
│   ├── serializers.py   # If using DRF
│   ├── admin.py
│   └── tests.py
├── requirements.txt
└── ruff.toml
```

## Views

For JSON APIs, use `JsonResponse`:

```python
from django.http import JsonResponse

def list_items(request):
    items = Item.objects.values("id", "name", "created_at")
    return JsonResponse(list(items), safe=False)
```

For class-based views:
```python
from django.views import View
from django.http import JsonResponse

class ItemListView(View):
    def get(self, request):
        items = Item.objects.values("id", "name")
        return JsonResponse(list(items), safe=False)
```

## Models

```python
from django.db import models

class Item(models.Model):
    name = models.CharField(max_length=255)
    description = models.TextField(blank=True)
    created_at = models.DateTimeField(auto_now_add=True)

    class Meta:
        ordering = ["-created_at"]

    def __str__(self):
        return self.name
```

Always create and run migrations after model changes:
```bash
python manage.py makemigrations
python manage.py migrate
```

## Environment Variables

Use `django-environ` for configuration:
```python
import environ

env = environ.Env()
SECRET_KEY = env("SECRET_KEY", default="change-me")
DEBUG = env.bool("DEBUG", default=False)
DATABASES = {"default": env.db("DATABASE_URL")}
```

## Health Check

Always include a health endpoint:
```python
def health_check(request):
    return JsonResponse({"status": "ok"})
```

## Static Files

Use WhiteNoise for serving static files in production:
```python
MIDDLEWARE = [
    "django.middleware.security.SecurityMiddleware",
    "whitenoise.middleware.WhiteNoiseMiddleware",
    # ...
]
```

## Linting

Run before committing:
```bash
ruff check --fix .
ruff format .
```
